<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1004,1138]" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">
This is the first formal record of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[719,790,1004,1030]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">China</collectingCountry>
. It is unique in that the shape of the paraproct apex is flat and broad, decorated with some strong setae giving the appearance of a brush. To date, this species has only been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[313,373,1076,1102]" name="India" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[384,486,1076,1102]" name="Thailand" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[544,633,1077,1103]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[644,715,1076,1102]" name="China" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">China</collectingCountry>
. However, it is quite possible that it may also occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1436,1077,1103]" name="Myanmar" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[198,297,1112,1138]" name="Vietnam" pageId="16" pageNumber="261">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
